Babel 250 (Hangul: 바벨250) is a South Korean reality television program on tvN, which first aired on July 11, 2016. The show features a cast of four men and three women, all from different countries, who live together as an experiment, speaking their own languages and attempting to create a universal one. The show's title is loosely based on the story of the Tower of Babel and 250 family of languages currently in use in the world.
On September 27, 2016, the first season ended with Episode 12.
